[SN]TITLE[SN]
Peterborough United 1-4 Charlton Athletic

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Championship Charlton continued their unbeaten start to the season with a comfortable win over League One Peterborough in League Cup round two.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Mikhail Kennedy put the visitors ahead early on in his professional debut.
Karlan Ahearne-Grant doubled Charlton's lead from the spot after a foul on Kennedy in the box after the break.
Ahmed Kashi added a spectacular third and Igor Vetokele made it four, before Jermaine Anderson headed a late goal for Peterborough.
